<updated>2015-11-18T21:05:27-07:00</updated>
<published>2015-11-18T21:05:27-07:00</published>
<id>http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=5383&amp;p=23625#p23625</id>
<link href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=5383&amp;p=23625#p23625"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Taskbar transparency and maximized windows]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=5383&amp;p=23625#p23625"><![CDATA[
What would be the purpose/functional enhancement of this change? Also note that Android does not have a taskbar that lets you switch directly between running apps, for that it has a task switcher. On Windows, one app can be maximized, other can be windowed, the user can rapidly switch between switch them. In this case, how will the taskbar behave? Will it change transparency every time you simply change focus to another app or open the Start Menu? It is not practical in a multitasking OS with overlapping windows like Windows. It will cause more distraction than be useful.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">Gaurav</a> — Wed Nov 18, 2015 9:05 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
